@dev create
      creates new exchange pairs between a baseToken
      (ocean token) and datatoken.
 datatoken refers to a datatoken contract address
 addresses  - array of addresses with the following struct:
                [0] - baseToken
                [1] - owner
                [2] - marketFeeCollector
                [3] - allowedSwapper - if != address(0), only that is allowed to swap (used for ERC20Enterprise)
 uints  - array of uints with the following struct:
                [0] - baseTokenDecimals
                [1] - datatokenDecimals
                [2] - fixedRate
                [3] - marketFee
                [4] - withMint

natspec.details: FixedRateExchange is a fixed rate exchange Contract      Marketplaces uses this contract to allow consumers      exchanging datatokens with ocean token using a fixed      exchange rate.

buyDT(bytes32,uint256,uint256,address,ui.details: swap      atomic swap between two registered fixed rate exchange.

params.datatokenAmount: the amount of datatokens to be exchanged
params.maxBaseTokenAmount: maximum amount of base tokens to pay

calcBaseInGivenOutDT(bytes32,uint256,uin.details: calcBaseInGivenOutDT      Calculates how many baseTokens are needed to get exact amount of datatokens

params.datatokenAmount: the amount of datatokens to be exchanged

calcBaseOutGivenInDT(bytes32,uint256,uin.details: calcBaseOutGivenInDT      Calculates how many basteTokens you will get for selling exact amount of baseTokens

params.datatokenAmount: the amount of datatokens to be exchanged

collectBT(bytes32,uint256).details: collectBT      Collects and send basetokens.      This function can be called by anyone, because fees are being sent to ERC20.getPaymentCollector

collectDT(bytes32,uint256).details: collectDT      Collects and send datatokens.      This function can be called by anyone, because fees are being sent to ERC20.getPaymentCollector

collectMarketFee(bytes32).details: collectMarketFee      Collects and send publishingMarketFee.      This function can be called by anyone, because fees are being sent to exchanges.marketFeeCollector

collectOceanFee(bytes32).details: collectOceanFee      Collects and send OP Community fees.      This function can be called by anyone, because fees are being sent to opcCollector

createWithDecimals(address,address[],uin.details: create      creates new exchange pairs between a baseToken      (ocean token) and datatoken. datatoken refers to a datatoken contract address addresses  - array of addresses with the following struct:                [0] - baseToken                [1] - owner                [2] - marketFeeCollector                [3] - allowedSwapper - if != address(0), only that is allowed to swap (used for ERC20Enterprise) uints  - array of uints with the following struct:                [0] - baseTokenDecimals                [1] - datatokenDecimals                [2] - fixedRate                [3] - marketFee                [4] - withMint

generateExchangeId(address,address).details: generateExchangeId      creates unique exchange identifier for two token pairs.

params.baseToken: refers to a base token contract address
params.datatoken: refers to a datatoken contract address

getBTSupply(bytes32).details: getSupply      gets the current supply of datatokens in an fixed      rate exchagne

getDTSupply(bytes32).details: getSupply      gets the current supply of datatokens in an fixed      rate exchagne

getExchanges().details: getExchanges      gets all the exchanges list

returns._0: a list of all registered exchange Ids

getId().details: getId      Return template id in case we need different ABIs.       If you construct your own template, please make sure to change the hardcoded value

getNumberOfExchanges().details: getNumberOfExchanges      gets the total number of registered exchanges

returns._0: total number of registered exchange IDs

getRate(bytes32).details: getRate      gets the current fixed rate for an exchange

isActive(bytes32).details: isActive      checks whether exchange is active

returns._0: true if exchange is true, otherwise returns false

sellDT(bytes32,uint256,uint256,address,u.details: sellDT      Sell datatokenAmount while expecting at least minBaseTokenAmount

params.datatokenAmount: the amount of datatokens to be exchanged
params.minBaseTokenAmount: minimum amount of base tokens to cash in

setRate(bytes32,uint256).details: setRate      changes the fixed rate for an exchange with a new rate

toggleExchangeState(bytes32).details: toggleExchangeState      toggles the active state of an existing exchange
